    <div class = "Network reveal", id = "Part2">
        <h2>Section 2</h2>


        <p id="Header2">
            An Enhanced Networking Approach  
        </p>

        <p id="Paragraph">
            Traditional NHLe models compute conversion factors based on the assumption <br> that players directly transition from their respective leagues to the NHL. However, prospects often play in multiple leagues before reaching the NHL.
            <br> <br> To solve this issue, newer NHLe models have employed the networking approach, which considers multiple pathways from different leagues to the NHL and combines conversion factors between leagues. Unfortunately, the networks include various transitions that players would not typically make, leading to inaccurate equivalency factors. For instance, they may account for transitions between multiple European and North American leagues, even though most prospects usually follow a fixed path through developmental leagues before reaching the NHL.
            <br> <br> The Revamped NHLe model analyzes the paths that prospects are most likely to take on their journey to the NHL. It thus reflects the actual development of prospects and provides more accurate equivalency factors.  
 
        </p>

        <div class = "flow_chart">
            <img src = "flow_chart.png">
