    <div class = "Projection reveal", id = "Part3">
        <h2>Section 2</h2>

        <p id="Header2">
            A New Lens into Prospect Projections
        </p>

        <p id="Paragraph">
        In contrast to newer models that assign probabilities to a player's potential based on their NHLe, this approach recognizes the limitations of a purely statistical approach. Although there is a strong correlation between NHLe and a NHL playerâ€™s success, player development is influenced by factors beyond point production, such as defensive skills, linemates and special team contributions.  
        <br> <br> The model provides a realistic projection for prospects by solely predicting their future point totals in the NHL. These predictions are derived from historical NHLe data of current players and adjusted to account for prospects of different ages. 
        <br> <br> To improve the accuracy of these projections, the NHLe model can be combined with traditional scouting reports, which offer valuable insights into player qualities that NHLe cannot capture. By combining statistical analysis and informed scouting, this model can provide more reliable evaluations of prospects.

        </p>

        <div class = "Will_Smith">
